observations.recommendation:
We recommend that Management:
a.) Require the Municipal Accountant and all department heads to comply with the provisions of Section 114 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs specifically on the recording of supplies and materials as Inventories. All purchases of supplies and materials should be taken up as Inventories except those purchases from the Petty Cash Fund;
b.)Require the Municipal Accountant to keep an updated Supplies Ledger Cards and the General Services Officer to maintain Stock Cards for each inventory item received which should be reconciled with the SLC in the Accounting department; 
c.)Require the GSO to prepare and submit the Report on the Supplies and Materials Issued monthly to the Accounting department for the recording of the utilization in the Journal Entry Voucher to adjust the Inventories accounts.
d.)Require the Municipal Accountant to support Liquidation Reports of Trust Funds with Utilization Report/distribution list and the like, duly acknowledged by the intended beneficiaries/recipients.

We recommend Management to:
    a. Require Oscar B. Nistal, the Project Development Officer, with Engr. Alexander P. Dolauta, the Municipal Engineer and Ma. Mercedes E. Salinas, the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator, the officials who prepared and recommend approval of the POW to explain the difference of the thickness of shouldering materials in the POW compared to that of the Approved Plans;
    b. Require the Inspection Committee to explain on their inability to note the difference of the actual accomplishment as against the POW that caused the payment of 100% project accomplishment when in fact it the material applied was only 98.71% of the programmed materials to be used for the project;
    c. Require the contractor to refund the amount of P11,811.00 pertaining to shouldering material not applied to the project.

We recommend that management:
    a.) Require the Municipal Accountant and all department heads to comply with the provisions of Section 114 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I specifically on the recording of supplies and materials as Inventories. All purchases of supplies and materials should be taken up as Inventories except those purchases from the Petty Cash Fund; 
    b.) Require the Municipal Accountant to keep an updated Supplies Ledger Cards and the General Services Officer to maintain Stock Cards for each inventory item received which should be reconciled with the SLC in the Accounting department;
    c.) Require the GSO to prepare and submit the Report on the Supplies and Materials Issued monthly to the Accounting department for the recording of the utilization in the Journal Entry Voucher to adjust the Inventories accounts;
    d.) Require the Municipal Accountant to support Liquidation Reports of Trust Funds with Utilization Report/distribution list and the like, duly acknowledged by the intended beneficiaries/recipients.

We recommend the Management to:
    1.) Strictly limit the charged wages of casual expenditures to the 55% PS; 
    2.) Refrain from providing additional Personal Services (PS) expenditures, until such time that the PS cap is observed as stated in Budget Circular No. 75, dated July 12, 2002;
    3.) Require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Budget Officer to charge wages of casual employees performing administrative/ clerical functions in the different offices of the municipality to its appropriate account Salaries and Wages- Casual (705) as provided in the Chart of Accounts under the NGAS;
    4.) Maximize the utilization of manpower (from regular employees) to avoid the need of hiring additional manpower (from casuals) in order not to exceed the 55% budgetary limitation for personal services;
    5.) Strictly adhere to proper classification of Personal Services transactions in order not to circumvent the rule on Personal Services limitation as provided in Section 325 (a) of the Local Government Code.

We recommend that management:
    a. Display notification before the start and while the projects are on-going in accordance with Annex A of the Circular with format and specifications;
    b. Strictly adhere to the other provisions of COA Circular 2013-004 attached hereto.

We recommend the Management:
    a.) Initiate the conduct of a complete physical inventory of the Municipality’s properties by creating an Inventory Committee composed of a representative each from the Mayor’s Office, the General Services Office (or the Municipal Treasurer’s Office) and a representative from each department to prepare the necessary procedures in the proper and orderly conduct of the physical count of all the property, plant and equipment and inventories owned by the Municipality;
    b.) Require the Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of all the properties recorded in the books and those not yet recorded but actually found in the LGU offices/premises and to prepare the corresponding inventory reports thereof; and reconcile them with the accounting records to come up with the correct account balances in the financial statement;
    c.) Require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain stock, property and ledger cards, respectively to properly account the receipt and disposition of property and supplies. The Office of the Municipal Treasurer should request additional staff for the conduct of the physical inventory.
